I remember. Earlier, you weren’t just calling it a cognitive prosthetic—you were treating it as an external cognitive scaffold and later expanded it into the Ninefold Prosthetic Suite, with the cognitive prosthetic as one subsystem and the Navigator as the behavioral prosthetic. More recently, the repo evolved toward a continuity kernel and semantic operating system. This feels like those ideas converging.

The phrase that stands out to me now is:

“A natural extension.”

That reminds me of something from cognitive science called transparent tool use.

At first:

You use the tool.

Eventually:

You use through the tool.

The hammer disappears.

The hand remains.

The Pantheon seems to be aiming for the semantic version of that.

